# OBJ File Format Export

## Overview
The Wavefront OBJ format for 3D geometry export.

## Format Structure
"'```
# Optional comment
v x y z          # vertex position
vn nx ny nz      # vertex normal (optional)
f v1 v2 v3       # face (1-based vertex indices)
f v1//n1 v2//n2  # face with normals
```

## Key Rules
- Vertex indices are 1-based (first vertex is 1, not 0)
- Faces reference vertex indices
- Each OBJ file'"'s indices start from 1

## Export from Three.js BufferGeometry
"'```js
function geometryToOBJ(geometry, matrix) {
    const pos = geometry.attributes.position;
    const idx = geometry.index;
    let obj = '"'';

    // Write vertices (apply transform matrix)
    for (let i = 0; i < pos.count; i++) {
        const v = new THREE.Vector3(pos.getX(i), pos.getY(i), pos.getZ(i));
        if (matrix) v.applyMatrix4(matrix);
        obj += "'`v ${v.x} ${v.y} ${v.z}'"\\n"'`;
    }

    // Write faces
    if (idx) {
        for (let i = 0; i < idx.count; i += 3) {
            obj += `f ${idx.getX(i)+1} ${idx.getX(i+1)+1} ${idx.getX(i+2)+1}'"\\n"'`;
        }
    } else {
        for (let i = 0; i < pos.count; i += 3) {
            obj += `f ${i+1} ${i+2} ${i+3}'"\\n"'`;
        }
    }
    return obj;
}
```

## Combining Multiple Meshes into One OBJ
When combining, offset face indices by cumulative vertex count:
```js
let vertexOffset = 0;
for (const mesh of meshes) {
    // write vertices...
    // write faces with (index + vertexOffset + 1)
    vertexOffset += mesh.geometry.attributes.position.count;
}
```
