# Three.js OBJExporter Usage

## Overview
Three.js ships with an OBJExporter in examples/jsm/exporters/OBJExporter.js.
This can be used as an alternative to manual OBJ generation.

## Usage
"'```js
const { OBJExporter } = require('"'three/examples/jsm/exporters/OBJExporter.js');
const exporter = new OBJExporter();
const objString = exporter.parse(object); // object can be Mesh, Group, or Scene
"'```

## Caveats
- OBJExporter applies world transforms by default
- When exporting a single mesh, it uses mesh.matrixWorld
- For part-local coordinates, you may need to manipulate transforms before export
- The exporter includes object names as `o meshName` lines

## Alternative: Manual Export
For precise control over coordinate space, manual vertex extraction is preferred.
See obj-format-export.md skill.
